<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:ns3="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="cv_thresh_binary_inverse" xml:lang="en">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>cv_thresh_binary_inverse</refname>
        <refpurpose>Binary Inverse operation</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Calling Sequence</title>
        <synopsis>image_ret =cv_thresh_binary_inverse(image)</synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Arguments</title>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>image</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Image that is to be inversely thresholded</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            
            <varlistentry>
                <term>image_ret</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Image is Inverse thresholded and given as output through "image_ret"</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>Provides Inverse Binary thresholding</para>
        <para>Thresholding is the simplest method of image segmentation.This function provides Inverse Binary thresholding which basically reverse of binary thresholding.
		This function takes an image as input and applies Inverse Binary Thresholding to the image. the Thresholded image is returned to User via output variable</para>
        </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example">image_ret=cv_thresh_binary_inverse(input_image)</programlisting>
		
    </refsection>
